Pronunciation: b A . r\ A N _ b A . r\ A N
Definition: Barang-barang is a Malay term commonly used in Singapore to various objects or things. It is pronounced as "ba-rang ba-rang" with a slight emphasis on the second syllable.
Example: 1. A: "Eh, where're all your barang-barang ah?" B: "They're in my bag, lah."
